  <h1>Privacy Policy for UIRS App</h1>
  <p><strong>Effective Date:</strong> November 26, 2025</p>

  <h2>Introduction</h2>
  <p>The Unified Incident Response System (UIRS) app is committed to protecting your privacy. This policy explains what information we collect, how we use it, how we protect it, and your rights regarding your data.</p>

  <h2>Information We Collect</h2>
  <p>We collect information to provide better incident reporting and response services. The information includes:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Personal Information:</strong> Name, email address, phone number and IDS provided when creating an account. </li>
    <li><strong>Location Data:</strong> Your GPS location when reporting incidents to ensure accurate response.</li>
    <li><strong>Incident Reports:</strong> Descriptions, images, and other media submitted during incident reporting.</li>
    <li><strong>Device Information:</strong> Device type, operating system, app version, and usage logs to improve app performance and troubleshoot issues.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>How We Use Your Information</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>To deliver app services and process incident reports effectively.</li>
    <li>To communicate with you regarding incidents, updates, or system notifications.</li>
    <li>To analyze app usage for improving features, security, and performance.</li>
    <li>To comply with legal obligations or respond to lawful requests from authorities.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>How We Share Your Information</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>We do not sell or trade your personal information to third parties.</li>
    <li>We may share your information with authorized emergency responders for accurate incident response.</li>
    <li>We may share anonymized or aggregated data for research, statistics, or system improvement purposes.</li>
    <li>We may disclose information if required by law or to protect rights, safety, or property.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Data Security</h2>
  <p>We implement appropriate technical and organizational measures to protect your information, including encryption, secure servers, and access controls. Access to personal data is restricted to authorized personnel only. Despite these measures, no system is completely secure. Users are responsible for protecting their own account credentials.</p>

  <h2>Childrenâ€™s Privacy</h2>
  <p>The UIRS app is not designed for children under 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13. If we learn that we have collected such information, we will delete it immediately.</p>

  <h2>Your Rights</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>You have the right to access, correct, or delete your personal information stored in our systems.</li>
    <li>You can request restrictions on how your data is used.</li>
    <li>You may withdraw consent for data collection at any time by contacting us.</li>
    <li>To exercise any of these rights, contact us at <a href="mailto:rogu.erdao.ui@phinmaed.com">rogu.erdao.ui@phinmaed.com</a>.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
  <p>We may update this privacy policy from time to time. Updates will be posted on this page. Please review this page periodically to stay informed about how we protect your data.</p>

  <h2>Contact Us</h2>
  <p>If you have questions or concerns about this privacy policy, contact us at <a href="mailto:rogu.erdao.ui@phinmaed.com">rogu.erdao.ui@phinmaed.com</a>.</p>
